This pre-owned or refurbished product has been professionally inspected and tested to work and look like new. How a product becomes part of Amazon Renewed, your destination for pre-owned, refurbished products: A customer buys a new product and returns it or trades it in for a newer or different model. That product is inspected and tested to work and look like new by Amazon-qualified suppliers. Then, the product is sold as an Amazon Renewed product on Amazon. If not satisfied with the purchase, renewed products are eligible for replacement or refund under the Amazon Renewed Guarantee.

Pre-owned Certified: Electronics

Pre-owned Certified products are inspected, cleaned and (if applicable) repaired to excellent functional standards. By purchasing pre-owned rather than new, customers can extend the life of the product, reduce electronic waste, and reduce the extraction of raw materials. These products are backed by the Amazon Renewed Guarantee. Pre-owned Certified is part of the Climate Pledge Friendly program that helps you discover and shop for more-sustainable products.

What should I expect to receive with my Amazon Renewed purchase?
All Amazon Renewed purchases will come with accessories equivalent to those that shipped in the box when new. These items may not be original but will be compatible and fully functional. Amazon Renewed products will be packaged in either original packaging or in a new and clean cardboard box.
In what condition can I expect my Amazon Renewed product to be?
Product will be restored to its original factory settings and will be in one of the following cosmetic conditions Premium, Excellent, Good or Acceptable. Learn more

      First off, the seller I got this from was great. Arrived on time. Watch didn't have a single scuff or smudge on it. Literally like new. Box is generic, but everything inside looks original including the charger and the manuals. The battery was a little low (56%) when I... See more
      First off, the seller I got this from was great. Arrived on time. Watch didn't have a single scuff or smudge on it. Literally like new. Box is generic, but everything inside looks original including the charger and the manuals. The battery was a little low (56%) when I got it, so I gave it a charge before set up and it was full in no time.

      Watch itself is great. Easy set up as long as you follow the directions and use the app. Picked a simple watch face and called it good. The main complaint I saw about this watch is the battery life. I read up before getting it and adjusted settings right off the bat. I don't keep the face on all the time (1. For battery life and 2. Some users had screen burn) I don't care much for the health things, so I have all preferences like the bpm monitor set to manual so I use them as I see fit instead of them either going continuously or every 10 minutes.
      If you have bad eyesight like me, use the large font setting
      And for the love of everything, download the Gboard app. Like literally right out of the box past set up, get it. Otherwise you have to use T9 and text like it's 2000 again.

      The only downside (for me) is I have tiny wrists and the standard band is way too large. There are large gaps on either side. This isn't really a downside, I just had to spend a little extra on a new band. No biggie.
      Over all, great watch. I may just get my partner one too. (It now has a walkie-talkie app!)

      3.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Great Watch. Charging and Battery life suck though
      Reviewed in the United States on May 29, 2023
      I love all the features this watch has to offer. It has so many way to customize it, and it does everything the average Fitbit does and more. It's not a bad price either. My biggest qualm with it is charging it. The magnet on the charger isnt very strong and doesn't... See more
      I love all the features this watch has to offer. It has so many way to customize it, and it does everything the average Fitbit does and more. It's not a bad price either. My biggest qualm with it is charging it. The magnet on the charger isnt very strong and doesn't hold the watch very well making it easy to bump it and stop the charge, or if you don't place it just right it won't charge at all. Another thing to mention is that you have to use a wall charger that only outputs 1 amp. Anything higher and the watch will freak out. I bought a refurbished watch and it didn't come with a wall charger or an instruction manual or anything so it took a lot of research to figure that out.

      Also the battery life is terrible. If you have the constant heart rate monitor and the raise wrist to wake feature enabled the battery dies within 16 hours, so you have to charge it every night which means you can't really use the sleep monitoring functions.

      Other than that the watch is great. I'd recommend doing some research though and if there is a later model with a better battery life, go for that one.
